subSubSection.paragraph:
The absence of a stenocostal area argues for the placement in Phatnomatini; however, the presence of occipital spines just in front of the eyes argues for the placement in Cantacaderinae. The frontal spines look like that which Lis (
1999
) called jugo-frontal spines, distinguishing Cantacaderinae. In addition, the jugal and clypeal spines are absent. This combination of spines would argue for the placement of the species in Cantacaderinae. However, the presence of an additional dorsomedial spine between the two paired ones rather argues for the placement of this species in Phatnomatini.
